SIMPLE: sphenethmoid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sphenethmoid
<hw>Sphe*neth"moid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sphen</ets>oid + <ets>ethmoid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to both the sphenoidal and the
ethmoidal regions of the skull, or the sphenethmoid bone;
sphenethmoidal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sphenethmoid bone</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>a
bone of the skull which surrounds the anterior end of the brain in many
amphibia; the girdle bone.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sphenethmoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sphenethmoid
<hw>Sphe*neth"moid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
sphenethmoid bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sphenethmoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
